VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
DRIVER DIES AFTER HITTING GUARDRAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 22-year-old man was killed after he fell asleep at the wheel of his car and 
hit a guardrail on the Ventura Freeway in Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
Arturo Castillo was traveling north Thursday on the Ventura Freeway near 
Westlake Boulevard when his car drifted onto the right-hand shoulder of the 
road and hit the guardrail, Officer Randy Klucker of the California Highway 
Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
Castillo, who was not wearing a seat belt, suffered arm fractures, broken ribs 
and internal injuries, Klucker said. He was taken to Westlake Medical Center in 
Westlake Village, where he died shortly afterward, Klucker said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
