<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 4 INJURED AS RTD BUS RAMS CAR ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A RTD bus slammed into the back of a car on the San Bernardino Freeway in West 
Covina Friday, sending it into a roll and injuring the car's driver and three 
bus passengers, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, Nick Veronica, 30, of El Monte, was in good condition at Queen of 
the Valley Hospital; the bus passengers were treated and released. 
</P>
<P>
The bus was westbound when it slammed into the car about 4:55 p.m., a 
spokeswoman for the West Covina Fire Department said. The collision pushed the 
car through a freeway barrier and sent it rolling over several times before 
coming to rest on North Garvey Avenue, parallel to the freeway. Veronica was 
thrown out and trapped under the car until two tow trucks pulled it off of him 
about 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
