<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
MAN, 40, ARRESTED IN COCAINE MAIL CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A yearlong narcotics investigation has culminated in the arrest of a 
40-year-old Ventura man on suspicion of transporting cocaine, authorities said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Alan Jeffrey Drettler was arrested at 10:55 a.m. Thursday as he drove along 
Telephone Avenue in Ventura, Ventura police officer Diane McCaskill said. 
</P>
<P>
Police have suspected for about a year that Drettler was mailing cocaine to 
Hawaii and Alaska, McCaskill said. 
</P>
<P>
He shipped a package to Sitka, Alaska, on April 19 and it was found to contain 
cocaine, McCaskill said. 
</P>
<P>
Drettler was being held in the Ventura Jail. Bail was set at $500,000. CAROL 
WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
