<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 3; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
97 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE SEEK MAN IN GAS STATION ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A armed man robbed a gas station in Ventura early Friday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The man approached the cash window at the College Mobile Service Station and 
Market on the 4100 block of Telegraph Road at 3:30 a.m. and demanded money 
after showing a handgun, Officer Bonnie Lucking of the Ventura Police 
Department said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman got away with less than $100, Lucking said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman is described as a black male, about 25 years old, about 6 feet tall 
and weighing 160 pounds, Lucking said. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman escaped in a mid-sized, two-door blue car, Lucking said. CAROL 
WATSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
