<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTH DAY FOCUSES ATTENTION ON DETERIORATION OF ENVIRONMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article by Kennedy is an example of the pathetic Pollyanna attitude that 
threatens to reduce the environmental movement to a media circus destined to 
quickly fade in deference to big business-as-usual. Earth First! should be 
applauded, not chided, for standing up to the vested interests and refusing to 
compromise the integrity of our remaining wilderness areas. 
</P>
<P>
It takes political and personal courage to chain oneself to a bulldozer or to 
physically block huge logging trucks in an effort to prevent further 
clear-cutting. The object of actions such as tree spiking is to protect 
forests, not injure loggers. Spiked trees are painted with large "S" as a 
warning. 
</P>
<P>
I applaud the more diplomatic efforts of Greenpeace, the Sierra Club and other 
mainstream environmental groups, but the question must be asked: "What have 
they really accomplished in the 20 years since the last Earth Day?" A series of 
politically palatable compromises and small victories designed by politicians 
and industry to pacify the public are all we have to show. The global 
environmental situation continues to worsen despite the well-intentioned 
efforts of these groups. Enough talk, Mr. Kennedy. It's time we put the Earth 
First! 
</P>
<P>
BRAD BOWLIN 
</P>
<P>
Hermosa Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
