<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTH DAY FOCUSES ATTENTION ON DETERIORATION OF ENVIRONMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Sunday we celebrated Earth Day. This day was to remind all of us that we 
must do something to save our planet from destruction, perhaps by recycling 
cans, plastics, glass. 
</P>
<P>
In general, do not pollute. 
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday morning I went out to get my paper and to my surprise found The 
Times wrapped in a large plastic bag. 
</P>
<P>
How can we save our world when large corporations, such as The Times, keep 
right on polluting? How many thousands of these bags will be found in landfills 
waiting hundreds of years to decompose? 
