<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEARCH FOR EXTRATERRESTRIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I must take issue with Konner's specious reasoning. He comes to the conclusion 
that "the likely result of contact is the most grotesque disaster that has ever 
befallen our species," the disaster being something on the order of what we 
humans have perpetrated upon animals within the melee of evolution. 
</P>
<P>
Konner assumes, therefore, that if we were to send messages to the stars, the 
likely consequence would be that the listeners would dispatch ships to come to 
Earth and enslave us or kill us all. 
</P>
<P>
His conclusion is derived from the assumptions that: Aliens have evolved 
exactly as we have; we represent a threat to their evolutional integrity, and 
they will conclude that the logical response is to come trillions of miles 
across space to deal with this threat. I hope people see this commentary for 
what it is -- misleading and ludicrous. 
</P>
<P>
JEFF SWANSON 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
