<HEADLINE>
<P>
HE WANTS SCULLY TO BE VINDICATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dan York of Laguna Hills (Viewpoint, April 21) could not possibly be talking 
about the Vin Scully I and many others grew up with. 
</P>
<P>
Although he has been often honored, I think that many still take Scully for 
granted. 
</P>
<P>
It is not enough to say that he is the best baseball broadcaster who ever sat 
behind the plate. Those of us who have lived with the company of Dodger radio 
broadcasts, while doing homework, driving in rush-hour traffic or just 
daydreaming at the beach, know how Vin Scully has touched our lives. 
</P>
<P>
Please, Vin, don't ever stop describing that high drive to deep left field. I 
still want to hear about Davis going back, awaaaay back, to the wall. And for 
as long as you can, I want you to tell me it's gone. 
</P>
<P>
GARY N. STERN 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 
