<HEADLINE>
<P>
KEATING'S YOUTHFUL ZEAL AGAINST PORN, OBSCENITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I had a hearty laugh when I read ("Mapplethorpe Show Bumps Into a City's Legacy 
of Conformity" by David Wells, Calendar, April 23) that Charles Keating, as a 
young Cincinnati attorney full of religious zeal, founded Citizens for Decent 
Literature and was later appointed by President Nixon to the Federal Commission 
on Obscenity and Pornography. The obscene greed displayed in the S&amp;L 
scandals is beginning to make sense. 
</P>
<P>
G. BORDING MATHIEU 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
