<P>
WEEKEND AT AFI FESTIVAL; 
</P>
<P>
SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Wilmington 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following are The Times' recommendations for today's and Sunday's schedule of 
the American Film Institute Los Angeles International Film Festival, with 
commentary by the film reviewing staff. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 480-3232 or (213) 520-2000. 
</P>
<P>
Highly recommended: 
</P>
<P>
"TWISTER"(U.S., 1989; Director: Michael Almereyda; Century Plaza, 4:15 p.m.). A 
strange and altogether fascinating comedy from writer-director Almereyda, his 
directorial debut. It's about a screw-loose Kansas family, and the cast is 
assembled like prize specimens in a zoo. Crispin Glover's performance is one of 
the great wacko characterizations in film. (P.R.) 
</P>
