Highly recommended: 
</P>
<P>
"KILLER OF SHEEP"(U.S., 1979; Director: Charles Burnett; AFI Mark Goodson, 2 
p.m.). This was the film that revealed Charles Burnett as one of our shy, 
stubborn poets, finding beauty and even hope in the rubble of the inner city. 
See this, which Burnett shot as well as produced, wrote and directed, for its 
remarkable performances, particularly Harry Gale Sanders, for its beauty, 
flashes of wit and amazing tensile strength. (Sheila Benson) 
</P>
