<P>
Following are The Times' recommendations for today's and Sunday's schedule of 
the American Film Institute Los Angeles International Film Festival, with 
commentary by the film reviewing staff. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 480-3232 or (213) 520-2000. 
</P>
<P>
Recommended: 
</P>
<P>
"LADDER OF SWORDS"(Great Britain, 1989; Director: Norman Hull; Century Plaza, 
6:45 p.m.). A husband-wife circus act on the skids in the British moors may not 
sound like a promising premise for a movie, but this debut feature is 
engagingly scruffy. The wayward lives it depicts are viewed without 
condescension. (Peter Rainer) 
</P>
