<TEXT>
<P>
Following are The Times' recommendations for today's and Sunday's schedule of 
the American Film Institute Los Angeles International Film Festival, with 
commentary by the film reviewing staff. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 480-3232 or (213) 520-2000. 
</P>
<P>
"THE AGITATORS"(Hungary, 1969; Director: Deszo Magyar; Fairfax, 6:45 p.m.). In 
this brilliant, hurtling portrayal of the abortive 1919 Hungarian rebellion, 
Magyar sees the past through a contemporary '60s prism: his young 
revolutionaries fulminate, rage, scream and slice each other's dialectics to 
shreds -- caught by a restless camera and slashing, propulsive editing. 
(Michael Wilmington) 
</P>
