<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BELGIUM; 
</P>
<P>
LIBYA DENIES PACT TO FREE 4 CAPTIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Libya denied reports that it reached agreement with Belgium over the release of 
four Belgians held hostage by Libyan-influenced, radical Palestinians. 
</P>
<P>
The Libyan Embassy in Brussels said Tripoli has "no link with the ongoing 
negotiations." The reports had said Brussels agreed to sign trade pacts with 
Libya and to free a jailed Palestinian. The Belgian hostages -- Emmanuel 
Houtekins, his wife, Godelieve Kets, and their two teen-age children -- were on 
a yacht in the Mediterranean in 1987 when they were seized by the Revolutionary 
Council of Fatah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
