<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Miller, former Colorado basketball coach, has been named coach at Army. 
Miller played at Army under Bob Knight. 
</P>
<P>
Miller, 41, replaces Les Wothke, who resigned April 7 after eight seasons and a 
record of 92-135 at West Point. 
</P>
<P>
Miller has a record of 105-164. He was 35-79 at Colorado and 71-85 at Cornell. 
</P>
<P>
In another coaching move, Jack Rohan, who retired as Columbia's basketball 
coach in 1974, was rehired after the first two choices turned down the job. 
</P>
<P>
Columbia, which has had only one winning season since 1979, offered the job to 
Seton Hall assistant coach Rod Baker, a former assistant coach at Columbia. 
After Baker turned it down, Rochester Coach Mike Neer also rejected it. 
</P>
<P>
Rohan, 58, compiled a 154-161 mark from 1961 to 1974, leading Columbia to its 
only Ivy League basketball championship in 1968. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Appointment 
</P>
