<P>
Five Wyoming football players charged with taking indecent, immoral or immodest 
liberties with a minor, were released from the Albany County Jail in Laramie 
after posting $10,000 bonds. 
</P>
<P>
They were charged in connection with an incident involving an 18-year-old 
female student that allegedly occurred April 7 in a university dormitory. Those 
under 19 are considered minors under Wyoming law. 
