<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
IN ANOTHER GROSSMONT 2-A GAME: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Valhalla 9, El Cajon Valley 5 -- Scott Lapinski had three hits and two RBIs and 
Greg Woodard had two hits and an RBI for Valhalla (12-11-1, 2-2). 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 3-A 
</P>
<P>
El Capitan 9, Monte Vista 8 -- Greg Ransweiler scored on a wild pitch with two 
outs in the bottom of the seventh inning to lead El Capitan (15-7, 3-0). Monte 
Vista is 14-9, 1-3. 
</P>
<P>
Granite Hills 10, Helix 9 -- Granite Hills (15-7-1, 2-1) scored five runs in 
the bottom of the seventh inning as Tom Koontz drove in the tying and winning 
runs. Helix is 12-8-1, 1-2. 
</P>
<P>
Palomar League 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 8, San Dieguito 2 -- The game ended under protest with two outs and 
the bases loaded for San Dieguito. Tony Sanchez, who had re-entered the game to 
play defense in the top of the seventh after being replaced by a pinch-runner 
in the sixth, did not officially check in with umpire Gary Mickle until 
reminded to do so by Coach Jerry Clements while batting with the count 1-2 in 
the bottom of the inning. A disagreement over the rules ensued between Mickle, 
Clements and Mt. Carmel Coach Sam Blalock, ending with Mickle calling Sanchez 
out. 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines 4, Poway 2 -- Shaw Henderson (4-4) no-hit seventh-ranked Poway for 
5 2/3 innings before Ed Thompson hit a two-run homer. Henderson finished with a 
two-hitter and seven strikeouts. Preston Bynes hit a three-run homer for Torrey 
Pines (10-11, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
Orange Glen 8, Fallbrook 5 -- Jim Roby homered, then came on to pitch in the 
sixth inning to save the game for Damon Vinje and the Patriots (13-8, 4-3). 
</P>
