<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
EVERYBODY WINS IN SPECIAL GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 540 athletes from central and north Orange County received gold medals 
after participating Friday in the Special Games at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Two students at Cal State Fullerton began the games in 1986 as a 
less-competitive version of the Special Olympics, said Mary Ann Faley, one of 
the games' volunteer organizers. 
</P>
<P>
"Our emphasis in this is they are all winners," Faley said. All participants 
are awarded gold medals and T-shirts no matter where they finished in the 
various events. 
</P>
<P>
This year, the special athletes competed in a softball and Frisbee toss, 
several running races, a long jump and an obstacle course. About 300 volunteers 
from the university and the community helped supervise the event. 
</P>
<P>
After the competition, athletes were treated to an afternoon barbecue, with 
food and supplies donated by local companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
