<P>
FREE CHILD GROWTH SCREENINGS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is your child the right size for his or her age? 
</P>
<P>
Learn the answer during a free screening of your child's growth and development 
today from 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. at Childrens Hospital of Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
A pediatric nurse will perform height, weight and blood pressure checks and 
provide educational materials on child development. 
</P>
<P>
Many parents are unaware that treatment is available for children with growth 
problems, said experts from the Human Growth Foundation, a group that studies 
these maladies. 
</P>
<P>
Sometimes growth disorders can be treated with a change in diet, foundation 
officials said. The free screening will be held on the second floor of the 
Medical Education Center in CHOC West, 455 S. Main St., Orange, on the corner 
of Main and La Veta Ave. 
</P>
