<P>
BOONE TO PLAY VOLLEYBALL FOR TROJANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aaron Boone of Edison High School has signed a letter of intent to play 
volleyball at USC this fall. 
</P>
<P>
Boone, a 6-foot-5 setter, will join former Orange County standouts Jason 
Perkins (Corona del Mar), Chris Knowles (Dana Hills) and Drew Sheward (Newport 
Harbor). 
</P>
<P>
"UCLA also wanted him but he had already made up his mind," Edison Coach Brian 
Rofer said. "UC Santa Barbara recruited him too, and I know a lot of other 
schools would have loved to have him." 
</P>
<P>
Rofer, who played volleyball at UCLA, said Boone has a chance to start as a 
freshman at USC. 
</P>
<P>
"In 1996 I think he has good shot at the Olympic team," Rofer said. "He'll be 
done with school by then and I can't see anyone touching him." MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
