<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESIDENTIAL BUILDING VALUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Kathie Bozanich and Elena Brunet / Los Angeles 
Times, Graphics by Doris Shields / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The value of home building permits issued in the county was up 5% over 1989's 
level. 
</P>
<P>
During the First two months of this year (the most recent information 
available), permits for $248.9 million were let. That's also the first 
year-to-year two-month increase since 1987. The January-February totals for 
1988 and 1989 were both 4% lower than the year before. Here's how the last five 
years compare: 
</P>
<P>
1986: $234,166 
</P>
<P>
1987: $259,336 
</P>
<P>
1988: $249,074 
</P>
<P>
1989: $238,090 
</P>
<P>
1990: $248,955 
</P>
<P>
Note: Amounts shown in thousands of dollars, not adjusted for inflation 
</P>
<P>
Source: Construction Industry Research Board 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Chart, RESIDENTIAL BUILDING VALUES 
</P>
