<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC SCIENTIFIC CEO ADDS 3RD TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paciffic Scientific Co. said Friday that its president and chief executive 
officer, Edgar S. Brower, has assumed the additional title of chairman. 
</P>
<P>
Brower replaces Harry R. Goff, who retired Wednesday at the Newport Beach-based 
company's annual meeting. 
</P>
<P>
Brower, 59, joined the company as president and director in June, 1985, and was 
named chief executive officer in December, 1985. 
</P>
<P>
Before joining Pacific Scientific, Brower was corporate group vice president at 
Allied-Signal Corp. and president of Allied Electronic Components Co. From 1972 
to 1977, Brower was assistant postmaster general of the United States. 
</P>
<P>
The company also elected Ronald B. Nelson and Charles L. Perry as corporate 
vice presidents, and John C. Dieckman as a board member. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Scientific makes electric motors and other industrial products, and 
fire detection and suppression systems for the aerospace industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
PACIFIC SCIENTIFIC CO; MANAGEMENT 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
